    "en": {
      "title": "Train running on Udara route is suspended",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Deputy Railway General Manager Mr. Gamini Seneviratne said today (2) that due to heavy rain, the train service between Colombo Fort and Badulla has been suspended due to the collapse of the mounds on the railway line between Nawalapitiya and Hatton on the Upland Railway and the train has been canceled for today (2) and tomorrow (3). ) said in the afternoon.",
        "Accordingly, the train scheduled to run from Badulla to Colombo Fort today at 6.00 pm, the three trains scheduled to run from Colombo Fort to Badulla tomorrow (3) morning and the three trains scheduled to run from Badulla to Colombo Fort tomorrow morning have been cancelled. said"
      ],
